I forgot to mentioned the Take Down Process
_
_
Please don’t disassemble and or Detangle your hair if you are in a rush or in an emotional state. We often take our own hair out by dry detangling and or rushing. Take your time, use leave in conditioner and water when needed for slip and ease. You’ll preserve so much hair this way. Be sure to get @brushwiththebest for the best detangling brush✨✨ #Wigs #weaves #sewin #boxbraids #twists #fauxlocs #lahairstylist

8 month loc journey 🔒 | what I’ve learned so far

✨ skipping out on instant locs or loc extensions allows me to see and feel what my natural hair is capable of and I love it.
✨ Less is more. Less products, less manipulation, less work, less worry
✨ Water is my friend. Shampooing once every 7-10 days helps the locing process. (I can finally enjoy getting caught in the rain)
✨ With shrinkage and swelling comes volume! Embrace the budding phase (it won’t last forever)
✨ the way people respond to my locs is really empowering…I wasn’t expecting that 🥰
✨Black women: we really limit our intimate experiences by not allowing our partners to touch our hair. Locs have given me that freedom back to be seen and felt for a deeper connection. We deserve this. 
✨THERE IS NO COMPARISON | no one’s journey will be like yours so focus on learning your hair and what it needs. This path is custom ☺️😉😘
_
_

The Mothership Collection! 

Queen More Life, along with her business partner in @morelifeliquid, @kaorinikstudios, have recently released a new collection of juices, The Mothership Collection!

@kaorinikstudios is the owner of a wellness brand called @afroveganbeauty that focuses on black owned, sustainable, clean products. For 6 years, she had been juicing and doing cleanses and began looking for a way to present it to the public. When a mutual friend connected her with Queen, the connection was perfect and the Mothership Collection came to life. 

Link Up with Michael Flix | There's More Life in the Liquids with Queen More Life. Available on YouTube link in bio.
